name: COVERAGE_4
description: The COVERAGE_4 table contains high-level information on both managed care and indemnity coverage records in your system. This table also contains information related to Health Insurance Marketplace and Medicare Advantage coverages.

columns.name: CVG_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the coverage record

columns.name: ALTR_ZIP
columns.description: The alternate ZIP code to which claims submitted under this coverage can be sent.

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_COUNTY_C_NAME
columns.description: The alternate county to which claims submitted under this coverage can be sent.

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_COUNTRY_C_NAME
columns.description: The alternate country to which claims submitted under this coverage can be sent.
entries: United States of ReCS

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_HOUSE_NUM
columns.description: The alternate house number to which claims submitted under this coverage can be sent.

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_DISTRICT_C_NAME
columns.description: The alternate district to which claims submitted under this coverage can be sent.

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_PHONE
columns.description: The alternate phone number for claims submitted under this coverage.

columns.name: ALTR_CVG_FAX
columns.description: The alternate fax number for claims submitted under this coverage.

columns.name: CVG_HEALTH_CENTER_C_NAME
columns.description: The category number of the health center for this coverage.

columns.name: CVG_CREATOR_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the user who created the coverage. This column is frequently used to link to the CLARITY_EMP table.

columns.name: CVG_ISOLATED_YN
columns.description: This flag is set if a coverage is isolated with regard to patient data restrictions.  Coverages created from isolated patients or isolated guarantors are flagged as isolated coverages

columns.name: SELF_VERIF_DATE
columns.description: Stores the last self-verification date. Used by Welcome.

columns.name: CONT_FROM_CVG_ID
columns.description: Points to a coverage that is logically the same coverage. This coverage record is continuing from the specified coverage record.

columns.name: HIX_POLICY_ID
columns.description: The exchange policy identifier

columns.name: MA_WORKFLOW_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: Keeps track of what state of the workflow the Medicare Advantage process is in.

columns.name: NUM_UNCVRD_MO
columns.description: The incremental number of uncovered months (NUNCMO). This is determined from the later of the prior part D date, last LIS date, or the member's Initial Enrollment Period (IEP) date. To get the total NUNCMO add this amount to the existing NUNCMO.

columns.name: PPO_C_NAME
columns.description: This value contains the premium payment option for a Medicare Advantage coverage. The premium payment option indicates whether the beneficiary has elected to withhold Part C and Part D premiums from their Social Security or Railroad Retirement Board (RRB) benefits, and if so, the type of withholding to use.  After running deferred conversion 767822, this column will be obsolete. The premium payment option will be available in table MCARE_PREMIUM_PMT_OPT.

columns.name: PART_D_OPT_OUT_YN
columns.description: This flag indicates that the beneficiary does not want Automated Enrollment in a Part D Plan. It applies to Low Income Subsidy beneficiaries who are subject to Automated Enrollment-Facilitated Enrollment into Part D.

columns.name: MMP_OPT_OUT_YN
columns.description: This flag indicates the beneficiary does not want passive enrollment into a Medicare and Medicaid Plan (MMP).

columns.name: ESRD_OVRIDE_YN
columns.description: This value indicates whether the End Stage Renal Disease (ESRD) override was used to enroll the beneficiary into a non-Prescription Drug Plan.

columns.name: CR_CVG_FLG_C_NAME
columns.description: This value indicates whether the beneficiary has creditable drug coverage in the period prior to enrollment in this Part D Prescription Plan. It is also used to reset the number of uncovered months to zero due to a new initial enrollment period (IEP) or laboratory information system (LIS) change and to remove resets that were set in error.
entries: Beneficiary does not have creditable coverage
Accumulated NUNCMO is reset to zero as of the effective date on the transaction
Previous reset is removed and total uncovered month accumulation is reinstated
Uncovered months reset to zero due to a new IEP
Uncovered months reset to zero due to a beneficiary Low Income
Cumulative uncovered months reset to zero because beneficiary enrolled in Part D plan and dual eligible

columns.name: EMPR_SUB_ENROLL_YN
columns.description: This value indicates that the beneficiary is currently in a plan receiving an employer subsidy, but still wants to enroll in a Part D plan

columns.name: ELECTION_TYP_C_NAME
columns.description: This value tracks the election type associated with the enrollment. The election type is associated with a particular election period, and a particular type might be limited to a certain number of usages per member. This value is only applicable to Medicare Advantage coverages.
entries: 5 Star Quality Rating Special Election Period
Open Enrollment Period for Institutionalized Individuals
Permanent Change in Residence Special Enrollment Period
Employer Group Health Plan Special Enrollment Period
Open Enrollment for Newly Eligible Individuals
Auto Enrollment, Facilitated Enrollment, Reassign Enrollment, or POS enrollment

columns.name: ENROLL_SRC_C_NAME
columns.description: This value indicates the source of enrollment, which is used only for Medicare Advantage coverages.
entries: Re-assignment submitted by CMS or Plan

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_F_NAM
columns.description: This item stores the first name of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. The system checks for mismatches between this name and the first name stored in the member record (EPT).

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_MID_INIT
columns.description: This item stores the middle initial of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. The system checks for mismatches between this initial and the initial of the middle name stored in the member record (EPT).

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_L_NAM
columns.description: This item stores the last name of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. The system checks for mismatches between this name and the last name stored in the member record (EPT).

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_GENDER_C_NAME
columns.description: The gender category ID for the gender of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. The system checks for mismatches between this value and the sex stored in the member record (EPT).

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_DOB_DT
columns.description: This item stores the date of birth of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. The system checks for mismatches between this date and the date of birth stored in the member record (EPT).

columns.name: BEQ_RESP_DOD_DT
columns.description: This item stores the date of death of the member as received from the CMS eligibility response file. An error is flagged if this is populated, since a deceased member cannot receive benefits.

columns.name: PART_A_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: This column stores the status category ID for the current Medicare Part A eligibility status of the coverage.

columns.name: PART_B_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: This column stores the status category ID for the current Medicare Part B eligibility status of the coverage.

columns.name: PART_D_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: This column stores the status category ID for the current Medicare Part D eligibility status of the coverage.

columns.name: PART_D_ELIG_STRT_DT
columns.description: This column identifies the date on which the beneficiary became eligible for Part D benefits.

columns.name: PEND_PPO_EFF_DT
columns.description: This column holds a future expected date on which the Pending Premium Payment Option (CVG-18566) becomes the Premium Payment Option (CVG-18567).

columns.name: PEND_PPO_C_NAME
columns.description: This column tracks what the new value for Premium Payment Option (see PPO_C) is expected to become as of the effective date given in PEND_PPO_EFF_DT.

columns.name: APCLM_CVG_VER_DATE
columns.description: Stores the date when the coverage was last verified. This data is only intended to be used when verification record (VRX) verification is used in an Accounts Payable (AP) Claims instance.

columns.name: DIS_ELECTION_TYP_C_NAME
columns.description: This value tracks the election type associated with the disenrollment. The election type is associated with a particular election period, and a particular type might be limited to a certain number of usages per member. This value is only applicable to Medicare Advantage coverages.

columns.name: HIX_CSR_SRC_CVG_ID
columns.description: This column is used to identify Cost Sharing Reduction (CSR) coverages and their corresponding source coverage (CVG) record. The value stored in this column is the ID of the source coverage of this CSR coverage. If the value is null, this coverage is not a CSR coverage.

columns.name: ADDR_CHG_USER_ID
columns.description: The user who initiated the linked address changes.

columns.name: ADDR_CHG_INSTANT_DTTM
columns.description: The instant that the linked address changes were initiated.

columns.name: ADDR_CHG_SOURCE
columns.description: The source record that initiated the linked address changes.

columns.name: ENROLL_GEO_VERIF_FAIL_YN
columns.description: Tracks coverages that have failed service/geographic area verification.

columns.name: SUB_ADDR_IS_UNDELIV_YN
columns.description: Indicates if subscriber home address is undeliverable.

columns.name: MA_WORKFLOW_STAT_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The reason for the Medicare status pertaining to a coverage.

columns.name: IN_NON_PREFERRED_AREA_YN
columns.description: If 'Y' then subscriber address associated with coverage was either only in a geographic area marked as "non-preferred" on the employer group or coverage was not in any geographic area linked to the employer group and employer group not configured to restrict enrollment by residency.  If 'N' or NULL, the subscriber address is in a geographic area linked to the employer group that is not marked as "non-preferred" or geographic area verification has not been run for this coverage.

columns.name: GEO_TERM_TRACK_DATE
columns.description: The date that geographic area verification based termination tracking has started for a coverage.  If not populated, coverage is not being tracked for termination.

columns.name: HIX_RENEW_COVERAGE_ID
columns.description: Stores the coverage ID that this coverage is renewing.

columns.name: EFF_DT_CHNG_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The effective date change reason at the coverage level.

columns.name: HIX_RENEWAL_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The exchange renewal type for the coverage.

columns.name: PAYMENT_TX_IDENT
columns.description: The payment transaction ID for the coverage.

columns.name: CARRIER_TO_BILL_BINDER_PMT_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the carrier (exchange) is responsible for collecting the binder payment for this coverage. 'Y' indicates that the carrier is responsible for collecting the binder payment. 'N' or NULL indicate that the carrier is not responsible.

columns.name: HOUSEHOLD_IDENT
columns.description: The household ID sent by the exchange for the coverage.

columns.name: MA_COVERAGE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores the types of Medicare covered by the managed Medicare coverage.

columns.name: PLAN_CHANGE_VERIF_PREV_CVG_ID
columns.description: The unique ID for the original coverage in the plan change.

columns.name: PLAN_CHANGE_VERIF_COMPLETE_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the plan change has completed execution for this coverage. 'Y' means the plan change has completed. 'N' means the plan change has not yet completed. NULL means this coverage is not the result of a plan change.

columns.name: ENTRY_DATE
columns.description: The date the coverage was created.

columns.name: EXISTING_NUNCMO
columns.description: The cumulative number of uncovered months (NUNCMO) as of the most recent prior Part D coverage. To get the total NUNCMO add the incremental NUNCMO to this amount.

columns.name: NUNCMO_SET_BY_C_NAME
columns.description: Captures how the NUNCMO was set

columns.name: PRIOR_PART_D_DATE
columns.description: The end date of the Part D coverage prior to this enrollment.

columns.name: MA_ENROLL_SEP_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The special election period reason used for enrollment on this coverage. This is required if the Enrollment Election Type is Other Special Election Period. This column can be linked to ZC_MA_ENROLL_SEP_RSN for additional information about the categories.
entries: Part D Disenroll for Other Creditable Coverage
Involuntary Disenroll from Loss of Part B
Cost Disenroll or Optional Supplemental Part D

columns.name: MA_DISENROLL_SEP_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The special election period reason used for disenrollment on this coverage. This is required if the Disenrollment Election Type is Other Special Election Period. This column can be linked to ZC_MA_ENROLL_SEP_RSN for additional information about the categories.

columns.name: MA_APPLICATION_CONFIRM_NUM
columns.description: The confirmation number associated with the Online Enrollment Center (OEC) enrollment application.

columns.name: MA_PLAN_CHANGE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category ID for the type of plan change that led to the creation of this coverage.

columns.name: MA_PLAN_CHANGE_COVERAGE_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the previous coverage that this coverage was created as a plan change from.

columns.name: GEO_AREA_INVEST_START_DATE
columns.description: The date when the coverage begins geographic area investigation.

columns.name: GEO_AREA_TEMP_ADDR_START_DATE
columns.description: The subscriber temporary address start date for this coverage.

columns.name: REQ_TRM_DATE
columns.description: Stores the original termination date requested when the advanced logic is applied to the coverage's termination date.

columns.name: TRM_NTC_DATE
columns.description: Stores the date that notice of termination was given to be used for advanced term date logic.

columns.name: CVG_PHONE2
columns.description: Payer phone number
